The paper discusses the design of AI systems from a user perspective, which is a key concern in the field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also emphasizes the importance of incorporating insights from social and behavioral sciences into AI design, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The focus on explainable AI and the need to understand, adopt, implement, and improve models aligns with the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's overall topic of AI design and user experience is most closely related to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
